---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Scrum Masters | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Scrum Masters working internationally, covering agile coaching positions abroad, scrum facilitation careers, and global tech team opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Scrum Masters";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Scrum Masters working abroad, facilitating agile teams internationally, and pursuing careers across tech companies, consultancies, and enterprises worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/scrum-master-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/scrum-master-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Scrum Master Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Scrum Masters facilitate agile development teams, remove impediments, and coach organizations in agile practices. International scrum master careers offer opportunities to work with global tech teams, spread agile practices, and experience diverse software development cultures.
      </p>
      <p>
        International scrum master opportunities exist through global tech companies adopting agile, multinational enterprises transforming to agile ways of working, agile consultancies operating worldwide, and the global spread of scrum methodology.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Scrum Masters working abroad across tech companies, consultancies, and enterprises worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Scrum Masters</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'Facilitation and conflict demands', typical: 'Often included' },
          { need: 'Voice coverage', why: 'Facilitation and coaching', typical: 'Consider for profession' },
          { need: 'Ergonomic coverage', why: 'Meeting and desk work', typical: 'Consider for profession' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Distributed team visits', typical: 'Depends on role' },
          { need: 'Wellness programs', why: 'High-interaction demands', typical: 'Often at tech companies' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Tech Company Benefits</h3>
      <p>
        Scrum masters typically work in tech companies or digital teams within enterprises. These employers generally provide comprehensive benefits including mental health support and wellness programs. Consulting scrum masters may have different arrangements.
      </p>
      <p>
        International positions often include relocation packages. The growing adoption of agile worldwide creates demand for experienced scrum masters, often with competitive compensation and benefits.
      </p>

      <h3>Facilitation Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Scrum masters facilitate meetings, navigate team dynamics, and manage conflict. This people-intensive work creates mental and emotional demands. Voice health also matters for the constant communication required in the role.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Tech Company</h3>
      <p>
        In-house scrum master. Tech benefits comprehensive. Team focused. Tech offers stability.
      </p>

      <h3>Consultancy</h3>
      <p>
        Agile consultancy. Firm benefits. Client variety. Consulting offers diversity.
      </p>

      <h3>Enterprise</h3>
      <p>
        Large corporation agile team. Corporate benefits. Transformation focus. Enterprise offers scale.
      </p>

      <h3>Startup</h3>
      <p>
        Growth-stage company. Benefits variable. Dynamic environment. Startups offer impact.
      </p>

      <h3>Remote</h3>
      <p>
        Distributed team facilitation. Self-arranged sometimes. Location independent. Remote offers flexibility.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Scrum Masters"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Scrum Masters working abroad across tech companies, consultancies, and enterprises worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Scrum Master Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Scrum Certification</h3>
      <p>
        CSM, PSM certifications. Scrum Alliance or Scrum.org. Entry credentials. Certification enables role.
      </p>

      <h3>Advanced Certifications</h3>
      <p>
        A-CSM, CSP-SM. Professional level. Experience required. Advanced certifications demonstrate expertise.
      </p>

      <h3>Agile Coach Credentials</h3>
      <p>
        ICAgile, Scaled Agile. Coaching competence. Enterprise agility. Coach credentials expand scope.
      </p>

      <h3>Experience</h3>
      <p>
        Team facilitation record. Transformation experience. Measurable outcomes. Experience validates competence.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Mental Health</h3>
      <p>
        Conflict navigation. Team dynamics. Emotional labor. Mental health support important.
      </p>

      <h3>Voice</h3>
      <p>
        Facilitation speaking. Coaching conversations. Meeting leading. Voice coverage consideration.
      </p>

      <h3>Ergonomic</h3>
      <p>
        Meeting rooms. Desk transitions. Standing facilitation. Ergonomic coverage valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Energy Management</h3>
      <p>
        High-interaction role. People-intensive days. Energy depletion. Self-care important.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Facilitation</h3>
      <p>
        Sprint ceremonies. Team meetings. Workshops. Facilitation is core work.
      </p>

      <h3>Coaching</h3>
      <p>
        Team coaching. Individual guidance. Agile mentoring. Coaching develops capability.
      </p>

      <h3>Impediment Removal</h3>
      <p>
        Blocker resolution. Organizational navigation. Problem solving. Removal enables flow.
      </p>

      <h3>Continuous Improvement</h3>
      <p>
        Retrospective leading. Process refinement. Practice evolution. Improvement sustains agility.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Global Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Agile adoption worldwide. Digital transformation ongoing. Skilled scrum masters valued. Demand strong.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Senior scrum master. Agile coach. Release train engineer. Transformation lead. Multiple paths.
      </p>

      <h3>Remote Potential</h3>
      <p>
        Remote facilitation growing. Digital tools enabling. Hybrid common. Remote increasingly accepted.
      </p>

      <h3>Methodology Evolution</h3>
      <p>
        Agile practices evolving. Scaled frameworks emerging. Continuous learning needed. Evolution ongoing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a scrum master considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Tech employers typically provide comprehensive benefits. Certifications transfer globally. Agile practices universal. Opportunities widely available.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do tech companies provide international coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Major tech companies yes. Comprehensive packages common. Relocation support often included. Verify specific offer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is mental health coverage important for scrum masters?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for facilitation demands. Conflict navigation stressful. People-intensive role. Mental health support valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Can I work remotely as a scrum master?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Increasingly yes. Digital facilitation tools available. Some prefer co-located. Remote growing.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do scrum certifications transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes, CSM and PSM globally recognized. Scrum practices universal. Certifications travel well.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Strong demand continuing. Agile adoption expanding. Digital transformation ongoing. Outlook excellent.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by evaluating employer benefits carefully. Ensure mental health coverage for facilitation demands. Consider voice coverage for communication-intensive work. Verify international coverage scope for relocation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Scrum Masters enable agile teams worldwide. Your coverage should support scrum master careers—addressing facilitation demands, covering health maintenance, and protecting you across agile work worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Scrum Master Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Scrum Masters working abroad across tech companies, consultancies, and enterprises worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
